                <h1>Duke Students and Workers in Solidarity, faculty members raise concerns about minimum wage increase</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/dc9584a4-8908-4186-85ca-9b909c789d45.sized-1000x1000.png?w=1000" alt="&lt;p&gt;One&#x20;of&#x20;the&#x20;demands&amp;nbsp&#x3B;issued&#x20;by&#x20;Duke&#x20;Students&#x20;and&#x20;Workers&#x20;in&#x20;Solidarity&#x20;in&#x20;the&#x20;Spring&#x20;was&amp;nbsp&#x3B;a&#x20;gradual&#x20;increase&#x20;of&#x20;the&#x20;minimum&#x20;wage&#x20;for&#x20;Duke&#x20;employees&amp;nbsp&#x3B;to&#x20;&#x24;15&#x20;an&#x20;hour&#x20;by&#x20;July&#x20;2019.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            <p>One of the demands&nbsp;issued by Duke Students and Workers in Solidarity in the Spring was&nbsp;a gradual increase of the minimum wage for Duke employees&nbsp;to $15 an hour by July 2019.</p>

                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
